STRING.10: The Metal Factory forges metal to produce units and buildings.
The Oil Pump draws Oil from the ground which is used to produce units and buildings.
Metal Storage houses metal for later use. Upgraded Metal Storage stores more tonnage.
Oil Storage keeps oil on reserve until it's needed. Upgrading Oil Storage increases the amount of barrels it can store.

The War Room is where intelligence data is analyzed post-recon, the hard calls are made and ideal strike locations are determined. Upgrade the War Room to extend your battlefield front, increasing your sphere of influence.
Planes and Helicopters are produced in Airfields. Airfield upgrades speed up production.
The Command Center is the hub for all activity on base. Upgrade the Command Center to unlock new buildings, upgrade existing buildings and enhance defense and resource structures.
Use Sandbags to fortify your base, protect key buildings and bottleneck the enemy. You can upgrade Sandbags to Concrete and Metal Blocks.

Rogue Factions love going to the Go-Go Bar. Crank the tunes and enemy units will come running. Take advantage of their eagerness and test your defenses. Pull the plug when you decide it's closing time.
Mortar Towers fire explosives into the air and rain down destruction on attackers. Upgrade the Mortar Tower to improve its range, damage and health.

Troops rely on the Bunker as a rally point when the going gets tough. Upgrading this defensive structure increases capacity and defense.
Laser Cannons' high intensity laser beams devastate both vehicles and planes. Upgrade the Laser Cannon to improve its range, damage and health.

Enemy troops may tread lightly, but they can't escape explosions. Once triggered, Light Mines deal large damage. Place these at choke points and near important buildings to bring death at enemy footfall.
Tesla Coils exterminate enemy vehicles by emitting disabling high voltage electric pulses. Upgrade the Tesla Coil to improve its range, disable time and health.
